faa-hf-std pack — content licence
==================================

This pack is derived from:
    FAA Human Factors Design Standard (HF-STD-001B)
    Federal Aviation Administration (US Department of Transportation),
    Human Factors Branch — HF-STD-001B, December 30, 2016

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work, 17 U.S.C. 105)  (tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

HF-STD-001B is a work of the United States Government, prepared by the FAA Human
Factors Branch and issued with the distribution statement "Approved for public release;
distribution is unlimited." As a US Government work it is NOT subject to copyright
protection in the United States (17 U.S.C. 105) and is in the public domain: anyone may
reproduce, transform, and redistribute it for any purpose, including commercially,
without permission. Attribution to the FAA is provided here and in the repository NOTICE
as a courtesy, not a legal obligation. The FAA does not endorse this pack or its authors.

THIRD-PARTY MATERIAL CAVEAT. HF-STD-001B is expressly a curated synthesis: nearly every
requirement is attributed in brackets to an underlying source, and the standard cites
and in places reproduces material from third-party copyrighted standards that are NOT in
the public domain — including MIL-STD-1472G, MIL-HDBK-759C and MIL-HDBK-761A,
MIL-STD-411 and MIL-STD-1800A, NUREG-0700, NASA-STD-3000A/B, ISO 9241, ANSI, BSR/HFES,
and TCO certification criteria — as well as US federal regulation (OSHA 29 CFR 1910/1926)
and internal FAA Orders. The copyrighted third-party material remains the property of its
respective publishers.

This pack reproduces none of that third-party material. It contains only synthesized,
transformed reference notes that NAME the cited sources and describe, in original words,
the FAA design criteria built on them. No third-party tables, exhibits, or long verbatim
passages are reproduced. The pack content was checked for verbatim overlap against the
extracted source text (check_overlap.py, runs of >= 12 words) and is clean.

Where HF-STD-001B's safety and environment provisions derive from OSHA and FAA
regulation, those regulations — not this pack — are the binding authority; this pack is
reference notes, not regulatory guidance.

NOTE: This file governs the CONTENT of this pack. The repository tooling is licensed
separately under MIT (see ../../LICENSE).
